WEBVTT

00:02.263 --> 00:05.135
ARE YOU THINKING
ABOUT HOW YOU'D STEAL IT?

00:05.222 --> 00:08.182
IT WEIGHS 2 TONS AND IS WORTH
MAYBE A COUPLE GRAND. PASS.

00:08.269 --> 00:09.574
BUT YOU WERE THINKING
ABOUT IT.

00:09.661 --> 00:12.099
IT'S AN INVOLUNTARY REFLEX.

00:12.186 --> 00:13.665
WELL, NATHANIEL ROLAND'S
INHERITANCE

00:13.752 --> 00:15.058
IS WORTH $40 MILLION.

00:15.145 --> 00:17.278
YOU REALLY THINK ONE OF HIS SONS
FORGED HIS WILL?

00:17.365 --> 00:20.150
PEOPLE DO SOME CRAZY THINGS
FOR MONEY.

00:20.237 --> 00:21.891
YOU THINK
THEY'D BE THAT STUPID?

00:21.978 --> 00:23.806
THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE GONNA FIND OUT.

00:23.893 --> 00:26.200
WELL, WHAT I'MGONNA
FIND OUT.

00:26.287 --> 00:28.419
YOU'RE SAYING I'M IRRELEVANT
IN THIS CASE?

00:28.506 --> 00:31.292
THE BUREAU REQUESTED THAT
I AUTHENTICATE THE WILL.

00:31.379 --> 00:32.902
I DON'T REMEMBER
YOU BEING MENTIONED.

00:32.989 --> 00:35.557
NOT ME?
NOT YOU.

00:35.644 --> 00:37.124
Man: RIGHT THIS WAY.

00:38.777 --> 00:41.215
HI. JOSH ROLAND. YOU'RE HERE
TO AUTHENTICATE MY WILL?

00:41.302 --> 00:42.607
AGENT PETER BURKE.

00:42.694 --> 00:45.001
MY ASSOCIATE NEAL
WILL TAKE A LOOK AT IT.

00:45.088 --> 00:46.481
I BECOME RELEVANT
IN A LITTLE BIT.

00:48.309 --> 00:49.832
HOW YOU DOING?
GOOD.
MAY I SEE THE WILLS?

00:49.919 --> 00:52.748
YEAH, THEY'RE BOTH HERE
ON THE TABLE.

00:52.835 --> 00:55.577
LOOK, I REALLY DON'T WANT HIM
TO GO TO JAIL OVER THIS,

00:55.664 --> 00:58.145
BUT IF HE'S TRYING
TO STEAL $40 MILLION...

00:58.232 --> 01:00.234
HEY, SORRY, I'M LATE.

01:00.321 --> 01:01.974
SAVANNAH'S NAP WENT A LITTLE
LONGER THAN EXPECTED.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.499
I DIDN'T TAKE A NAP.Shh.

01:04.586 --> 01:06.109
WHY DON'T YOU GO UPSTAIRS
AND PLAY, OKAY?

01:06.196 --> 01:07.241
SEE YOU IN A FEW MINUTES.

01:07.328 --> 01:08.546
HI, UNCLE JOSH!

01:08.633 --> 01:09.678
HI, SWEETHEART.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.941
MWAH!

01:12.028 --> 01:13.638
HOW YOU DOING?
I'M JAMES.

01:13.725 --> 01:14.726
NEAL.

01:14.813 --> 01:17.773
HELLO.
HI.

01:17.860 --> 01:19.557
James: I DON'T KNOW WHAT
MY BROTHER'S BEEN TELLING YOU,

01:19.644 --> 01:21.733
BUT I HAVEN'T BEEN
DOCTORING UP ANYTHING.

01:21.820 --> 01:23.779
THERE'S NO WAY DAD WOULD
HAVE LEFT YOU EVERYTHING.

01:23.866 --> 01:25.868
YOU'D SQUANDER IT.SQUANDER IT?
THAT'S A GOOD WORD.

01:25.955 --> 01:27.609
DON'T YOU MEAN
I'D BLOW IT?

01:27.696 --> 01:29.437
MAYBE USE SOME OF THIS
FAMILY'S MONEY TO DO
SOME GOOD FOR A CHANGE?

01:29.524 --> 01:30.916
DAD'S CHARITABLE
FOUNDATION --
TAX DODGES.

01:31.003 --> 01:32.266
ARE THEY ALWAYS
LIKE THIS?
YEAH.

01:32.353 --> 01:33.919
Josh: YOU'RE SAYING THAT
WITH FBI AGENTS IN THE ROOM?

01:34.006 --> 01:35.269
ANYWAY, MIND IF WE GET THIS
OVER WITH?

01:35.356 --> 01:36.792
YEAH.

01:36.879 --> 01:39.316
Savannah: WHO'S HE?

01:39.403 --> 01:42.058
HIS NAME IS NEAL.
HE KNOWS A LOT OF STUFF.

01:42.145 --> 01:44.234
WHAT'S THAT THING
ON HIS LEG?

01:44.321 --> 01:45.627
THAT'S A TRACKING
ANKLET.

01:45.714 --> 01:47.716
I HAVE AN ANKLET.
WANT TO SEE?

01:47.803 --> 01:49.587
YEAH. OH, CUTE.

01:49.674 --> 01:52.416
WHERE'D YOU GET IT?MY GRANDPA.
WHERE'D HE GET HIS?

01:52.503 --> 01:54.723
IT'S PART OF A FEDERAL
WORK-RELEASE PROGRAM

01:54.810 --> 01:56.464
WHERE...

01:56.551 --> 01:58.640
UH...
I GAVE IT TO HIM.

01:58.727 --> 02:00.729
IT'S SO I DON'T LOSE HIM.

02:00.816 --> 02:03.035
OH. ARE YOU HIS GRANDPA?

02:03.123 --> 02:04.428
WEREN'T YOU SUPPOSED TO GO
TO YOUR ROOM?

02:04.515 --> 02:05.734
UH-HUH.

02:05.821 --> 02:06.865
[ GIGGLES ]
UH-HUH.

02:06.952 --> 02:08.345
Josh:
HIS IS A FORGERY, RIGHT?

02:08.432 --> 02:10.217
THIS IS A FORGERY.

02:10.304 --> 02:11.305
James: WHAT?
I KNEW IT.

02:11.392 --> 02:12.871
HOLD ON.

02:12.958 --> 02:14.917
SO IS THIS ONE.THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

02:15.004 --> 02:16.310
THEY'RE BOTH FORGED?YEAH.

02:16.397 --> 02:17.963
HOW CAN YOU SAY
THEY'RE BOTH FAKE?

02:18.050 --> 02:19.269
THE WITNESS SIGNATURES --

02:19.356 --> 02:21.010
THE VELOCITY, ACCELERATION,
AND PRESSURE

02:21.097 --> 02:22.838
BOTH HAVE EXACTLY
THE SAME ANOMALIES.

02:22.925 --> 02:24.970
THEY WERE SIGNED
BY THE SAME PERSON.SO, WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

02:25.057 --> 02:27.582
Peter: BEFORE WE JUMP
TO ANY CONCLUSIONS,

02:27.669 --> 02:29.975
WE NEED TO VERIFY
THE WITNESS SIGNATURES.

02:30.062 --> 02:32.413
WE'LL RUN A COUPLE MORE TESTS.
WHEN WE GET SOMETHING...

02:33.762 --> 02:34.850
...WE WILL LET YOU KNOW.

02:34.937 --> 02:36.591
THANK YOU.

02:41.291 --> 02:43.815
[ SIREN WAILS, HORN HONKS ]

02:48.080 --> 02:49.908
DO I WANTTO KNOW
WHAT'S IN THAT BOX?

02:49.995 --> 02:53.564
WELL, TO PARAPHRASE THE MAN WHO
BROUGHT DOWN THE SOVIET UNION,

02:53.651 --> 02:56.567
IT'S EASIER TO TRUST
WHEN YOU CAN VERIFY.

02:56.654 --> 02:58.482
[ FANFARE PLAYS]

02:58.569 --> 03:00.441
YOU GONNA SHOW ME
A SHINING CITY ON A HILL? HMM.

03:00.528 --> 03:02.138
SHINING, YES, AND WITH IT,

03:02.225 --> 03:05.141
YOU CAN BUY ANY CITY
ON ANY HILL.

03:05.228 --> 03:06.838
A TREASURE-CAM?

03:06.925 --> 03:08.884
LOOK, I KNOW HOW HARD
IT MUST BE

03:08.971 --> 03:10.538
TO SEE THE PROMISED LAND

03:10.625 --> 03:13.018
AND NOT BE ABLE TO ENTER
BECAUSE OF YOUR LEASH,

03:13.105 --> 03:15.020
AND I DON'T WANT THIS
TO COME BETWEEN US.

03:15.107 --> 03:19.634
SO NOW, WE CAN BOTH KEEP AN EYE
ON OUR FORTUNE 24/7.

03:19.721 --> 03:20.939
THANK YOU, MOZ.
MM.

03:21.026 --> 03:22.941
OH. SEE THE DEGAS?

03:23.028 --> 03:24.987
YEAH.THINK I'VE LINED UP A BUYER.

03:25.074 --> 03:26.554
KIND OF HAD MY EYE
ON THAT ONE.

03:26.641 --> 03:28.556
OH, WELL, FORTUNATELY,
THERE'S TWO OTHER DEGAS

03:28.643 --> 03:30.558
TO CHOOSE FROM, MISTER...

03:30.645 --> 03:32.516
DID YOU PICK A NAME?
CLOSE.

03:32.603 --> 03:35.258
GLENN CLOSE?NO, I'M WORKING ON IT.

03:35.345 --> 03:38.305
MIGHT HAVE TO LIVE WITH
THIS NEXT ONE TILL THE END.

03:38.392 --> 03:40.089
WANT TO MAKE SURE IT FEELS
AS GOOD AS "NEAL CAFFREY."

03:40.176 --> 03:42.439
[ CHUCKLES ]
A ROSE BY ANY OTHER NAME, NEAL.

03:42.526 --> 03:44.441
CHOOSE, BECAUSE, VERY SOON,

03:44.528 --> 03:48.793
WE'RE GONNA BE ON AN AIRPLANE
TO A DIFFERENT LIFE.

03:54.277 --> 03:55.539
[ HORN HONKS ]

03:55.626 --> 03:57.324
HEY.

03:57.411 --> 04:00.631
WE GOT BACK BIOMETRICS ON
ROLAND'S WITNESS SIGNATURES.

04:00.718 --> 04:02.111
THEY ARE DEFINITELY
FORGED.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.330
COULD'VE TOLD YOU THAT.

04:03.417 --> 04:05.114
OH, WAIT. I DID.

04:05.201 --> 04:07.290
YEAH, AND BASED
ON YOUR OBSERVATIONS,

04:07.377 --> 04:09.205
WE RAN A COUPLE
OTHER TESTS.

04:09.292 --> 04:12.556
SEE HOW THE "A" IS CONNECTED
TO THE "E" TWO LETTERS LATER?

04:12.643 --> 04:14.689
AS ROLAND DID
IN HIS YOUTH.

04:16.821 --> 04:18.388
ROLAND FORGED
THE WITNESS SIGNATURES?

04:18.475 --> 04:19.955
ON BOTH WILLS
TO HIS CHILDREN.

04:20.042 --> 04:21.870
HOW DID I MISS THIS?

04:21.957 --> 04:23.741
YOU DIDN'T KNOW
HE WAS AMBIDEXTROUS.

04:23.828 --> 04:25.134
HE SIGNED THESE
WITH HIS LEFT HAND.

04:25.221 --> 04:26.875
AND THE NAMES ARE WEIRD.

04:26.962 --> 04:30.139
HORACE BYTH?
HATCH O'BREY?

04:30.226 --> 04:32.097
IT SOUNDS LIKE THEY'RE RIPPED
FROM A SALINGER NOVEL.

04:32.184 --> 04:34.796
WELL,
THEY ARE FICTIONAL.

04:34.883 --> 04:36.276
WHAT DO YOU SEE?

04:36.363 --> 04:39.191
THE SAME LETTERS.
THEY'RE ANAGRAMS.

04:52.248 --> 04:53.597
TYCHO BRAHE.TYCHO BRAHE.

04:53.684 --> 04:54.990
15th-CENTURY
DUTCH ASTRONOMER.

04:55.077 --> 04:57.340
16th AND DANISH. CLOSE, THOUGH.
ALMOST IMPRESSIVE.

04:57.427 --> 04:59.429
WELL, WELL.
WHO IS RELEVANT NOW?

04:59.516 --> 05:03.738
WHAT KIND OF MESSAGE
DO YOU THINK HE WAS
TRYING TO LEAVE BEHIND?

05:03.825 --> 05:05.696
HE CLOSES BOTH WILLS
WITH THE LINE,

05:05.783 --> 05:08.743
"IN THE END, THERE SHOULD
BE NOTHING BETWEEN YOU,
WHICH IS EVERYTHING."

05:08.830 --> 05:09.526
CRYPTIC.

05:11.180 --> 05:12.399
WAIT A SECOND.

05:18.187 --> 05:20.102
Peter:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

05:21.973 --> 05:24.411
Neal: INTERESTING.

05:24.498 --> 05:26.326
PETER, COME HERE.

05:28.502 --> 05:31.418
THESE LOOK LIKE STREETS.
A COMPASS ROSE.

05:31.505 --> 05:34.682
THIS ISN'T A MESSAGE.

05:34.769 --> 05:37.162
THIS IS A MAP.

05:58.488 --> 06:00.403
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

06:00.490 --> 06:02.666
JONES,
TELL ME SOMETHING.

06:02.753 --> 06:04.233
WHO IS THAT?Jones: EASY, TIGER.

06:04.320 --> 06:05.495
SHE'S OFF LIMITS.

06:05.582 --> 06:07.149
I ALREADY TRIED.
HUH.

06:07.236 --> 06:08.716
ART CRIMES, D.C.

06:08.803 --> 06:10.413
W-WHAT MAKES YOU
THINK THAT?

06:10.500 --> 06:12.676
HER ATTACHÃ©.
IT'S FROM THE SMITHSONIAN.

06:12.763 --> 06:16.245
GIFT OF CHOICE FROM D.C. ART
CRIMES CHIEF TO NEW RECRUITS.

06:16.332 --> 06:17.420
WHAT'S THE CASE?

06:17.507 --> 06:20.336
ABOVE MY PAY GRADE.

06:22.904 --> 06:24.949
Peter: YOUR BOSS AND I
GO BACK A LONG WAY.

06:25.036 --> 06:26.777
AGENT KRAMER'S SORRY
HE CAN'T BE HERE IN PERSON,

06:26.864 --> 06:28.170
BUT HE BRIEFED ME FULLY.

06:28.257 --> 06:29.345
HE DID?

06:29.432 --> 06:31.042
I TAKE IT
HE WASN'T SUPPOSED TO.

06:31.129 --> 06:32.696
HOW MUCH DO YOU KNOW?

06:32.783 --> 06:34.306
YOU DISCOVERED
A GERMAN U-BOAT

06:34.394 --> 06:36.439
WITH AN INCREDIBLY VALUABLE
CARGO OF ART ABOARD,

06:36.526 --> 06:38.093
THE ART WAS DESTROYED
IN A FIRE,

06:38.180 --> 06:40.400
BELIEVE THE FIRE
MAY HAVE BEEN A RUSE,

06:40.487 --> 06:42.489
AND THE ART STILL EXISTS.

06:42.576 --> 06:43.751
YOU KNOW A LOT.

06:43.838 --> 06:45.361
I'M SORRY. I DO.

06:45.448 --> 06:47.798
ONLY A HANDFUL OF PEOPLE
KNOW ABOUT THIS.

06:47.885 --> 06:49.234
I'D LIKE TO KEEP IT
THAT WAY.

06:49.321 --> 06:52.107
UNDERSTOOD.

06:52.194 --> 06:54.762
I DON'T HAVE ENOUGH EVIDENCE
TO OPEN A FORMAL INVESTIGATION.

06:54.849 --> 06:57.808
HOWEVER, PART OF THE ORIGINAL
GERMAN ART MANIFEST

06:57.895 --> 06:59.419
SURVIVED THE FIRE.

06:59.506 --> 07:02.422
THAT'S WHAT I'D LIKE KRAMER
TO LOOK INTO.

07:02.509 --> 07:04.424
NOW, WHAT I'D LIKE YOU TO DO
IS SIMPLY...

07:26.446 --> 07:28.709
EXCUSE ME.
DO YOU WORK HERE?

07:28.796 --> 07:30.493
NO. I DON'T.

07:30.580 --> 07:32.887
NO. OH, OF COURSE YOU DON'T.
I NOTICED YOUR ATTACHÃ©.

07:32.974 --> 07:34.932
YOU'RE, UH, D.C. ART CRIMES,
RIGHT?

07:35.019 --> 07:36.281
VERY GOOD.

07:37.805 --> 07:39.459
WHAT BRINGS YOU UP HERE?

07:39.546 --> 07:40.503
BUSINESS.

07:40.590 --> 07:41.809
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

07:41.896 --> 07:43.724
HEY, DO YOU KNOW WHERE
I CAN FIND AGENT BURKE?

07:43.811 --> 07:45.203
OH, I CANHELP YOU
WITH THAT.

07:45.290 --> 07:46.988
OFFICE AT THE TOP
OF THE STAIRS.
THANK YOU...

07:47.075 --> 07:48.337
AGENT MATTHEWS.

07:48.424 --> 07:49.904
AGENT MATTHEWS, YES.

07:52.297 --> 07:54.038
YOU'RE RIGHT, MAN.
I GOT NOTHING.

07:54.125 --> 07:55.692
TOLD YOU SO.

07:55.779 --> 07:57.128
TOP O' THE MORNIN', NEAL.

07:57.215 --> 07:59.435
APPARENTLY NOT.

07:59.522 --> 08:00.654
AM I LATE?

08:00.741 --> 08:01.959
RIGHT ON TIME.

08:02.046 --> 08:03.395
I SPOKE WITH THE ROLANDS.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.658
YOU TELL THEM
ABOUT THE MAP?

08:04.745 --> 08:05.963
I WANTED TO WAIT FOR YOU.

08:06.050 --> 08:07.617
YOU'RE GOING TO SEE THEM?MM-HMM.

08:09.445 --> 08:10.838
YOU'RE A LITTLE GIDDY.

08:10.925 --> 08:12.361
I LOVE PUZZLES.
I KNOW YOU DO.

08:12.448 --> 08:14.189
I'VE SEEN THE NEW YORK
PUZZLETHON TROPHIES

08:14.276 --> 08:16.060
AROUND THE HOUSE,
ALL THREE OF THEM.
FOUR.

08:16.147 --> 08:17.105
OH, THERE'S FOUR?
YEAH.

08:17.192 --> 08:19.150
HOW COULD I FORGET?

08:19.237 --> 08:21.762
Peter: THE OVERLAID WILLS
FORM AN IMAGE.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.633
THAT'S THE SUNDIAL
IN LE MONDE GARDEN.

08:26.723 --> 08:29.291
[ SIGHS ] WE HAVEN'T DONE
ONE OF THOSE IN YEARS.

08:29.378 --> 08:31.249
ONE OF THOSE
TREASURE HUNTS?

08:31.336 --> 08:32.424
YEP.

08:34.122 --> 08:34.992
TOLD YOU IT WAS A MAP.

08:35.079 --> 08:36.124
I DIDN'T SAY IT WASN'T.

08:36.211 --> 08:37.604
WELL, FORGET IT.

08:37.691 --> 08:39.606
I'LL SEE YOU IN COURT.

08:43.174 --> 08:45.612
HE'S ALWAYS BEEN HIGH-STRUNG.
YOU KNOW, WHATEVER.

08:45.699 --> 08:47.701
WHY DON'T WE TAKE A LOOK
AT THE SUNDIAL?

08:47.788 --> 08:49.529
THE REAL WILL IS AT THE END
OF THE HUNT, RIGHT?

08:49.616 --> 08:51.052
YEAH, MAYBE.

08:51.139 --> 08:54.229
I GOT TO GO, GUYS.
SAVANNAH'S GONNA BE HOME SOON.

08:54.316 --> 08:56.361
MY FATHER'S GONE.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.189
WE DON'T HAVE TO PLAY
BY HIS RULES ANYMORE.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.414
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT NOW?

09:05.501 --> 09:06.937
LOG THESE INTO EVIDENCE

09:07.024 --> 09:10.071
AND RETURN THEM
TO THE LAWYERS.

09:10.158 --> 09:12.160
MM-HMM, YOU'RE NOT
EVEN A LITTLE BIT CURIOUS

09:12.247 --> 09:13.509
ABOUT SOLVING
THIS PUZZLE?

09:13.596 --> 09:15.598
OF COURSE I AM, BUT, YOU KNOW,
THE ASSISTANT DIRECTOR

09:15.685 --> 09:17.992
HASN'T AUTHORIZED AN FBI
TREASURE-HUNTING UNIT.

09:18.079 --> 09:19.515
WELL, WHY DON'T WE
DROP BY THE PARK?

09:19.602 --> 09:22.126
JUST TO MAKE SURE NOTHING
ILLICIT IS AFOOT AT THE SUNDIAL.

09:22.213 --> 09:25.477
I CAN'T. I HAVE LUNCH WITH EL.
BUT YOU CAN TAKE A LOOK.

09:25.565 --> 09:27.784
YOU DON'T WANT TO COME?
YES.

09:27.871 --> 09:29.873
I COULD USE YOUR ASTRONOMICAL
PUZZLING EXPERTISE.

09:29.960 --> 09:32.136
OH.

09:32.223 --> 09:33.616
NO, I CAN'T. I CAN'T.
I CAN'T.

09:33.703 --> 09:35.792
EL HAD AN INTERVIEW
THIS MORNING.
AH.

09:35.879 --> 09:37.794
THERE'S AN OPENING
AT THE DeARMITT GALLERY.

09:37.881 --> 09:39.491
HOW NICE.
YEAH.

09:39.579 --> 09:40.841
NEXT TIME.

09:40.928 --> 09:42.799
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
JUST, YOU KNOW...

09:42.886 --> 09:44.279
KEEP ME UPDATED.

09:44.366 --> 09:46.281
MM-HMM.

09:52.940 --> 09:54.245
[ HORN HONKS ]

09:54.332 --> 09:57.379
Mozzie: FASCINATING.
THE COMPLEXITY.

09:57.466 --> 09:59.860
THESE PATTERNS MUST HAVE TAKEN
WEEKS TO DEVISE.

09:59.947 --> 10:01.122
AH.

10:01.209 --> 10:04.038
ROLAND IS LIKE
A COPERNICAN CROSS

10:04.125 --> 10:07.171
BETWEEN DAN BROWN
AND SCOTT TUROW.

10:07.258 --> 10:09.565
I THINK THESE NUMBERS
ARE TIMES OF DAY.

10:09.652 --> 10:11.349
4:30.

10:11.436 --> 10:13.090
Mozzie:
THAT WOULD BE THERE.

10:16.485 --> 10:18.661
DOESN'T SEEM
TO POINT TO ANYTHING.

10:18.748 --> 10:20.707
WELL, EVERYTHING POINTS
TO SOMETHING.

10:20.794 --> 10:22.186
DID YOU JUST STEAL THAT
FROM MY BRAIN?

10:22.273 --> 10:23.884
NO.

10:23.971 --> 10:25.973
WE'RE MISSING
SOME DETAIL.

10:26.060 --> 10:27.714
WHAT DO YOU THINK HAPPENS
WHEN THE SUN HITS IT?

10:27.801 --> 10:29.237
FOUR HOURS TO FIND OUT.

10:29.324 --> 10:30.717
Peter: HOW'D IT GO
AT THE GALLERY?

10:30.804 --> 10:32.066
MM. GOOD.
YEAH?

10:32.153 --> 10:34.111
YEAH, THEY'RE LOOKING
FOR A CONSULTANT.

10:34.198 --> 10:36.113
SO, I DON'T KNOW.
I WAS THINKING...

10:36.200 --> 10:37.593
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]WOW.

10:37.680 --> 10:38.942
"WOW"?

10:39.029 --> 10:40.640
NO.
I-I WAS WOWING YOUR NEWS.

10:40.727 --> 10:42.380
I DON'T NEED
TO ANSWER THAT.

10:42.467 --> 10:44.513
SWEETIE, IF IT'S WORK...IT'S NOTHING.

10:44.600 --> 10:47.385
SO, UH, COULD YOU -- COULD YOU
CONSULT AT THE GALLERY

10:47.472 --> 10:48.996
AND STILL DO BURKE EVENTS?

10:49.083 --> 10:50.388
YEAH, I THINK
I COULD DO BOTH.

10:50.475 --> 10:52.086
AND, BESIDES, I COULD DO
MY OWN OPENINGS.

10:52.173 --> 10:53.522
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]I DON'T KNOW.

10:53.609 --> 10:55.524
YOU SHOULD DO THIS.
YOU SHOULD DO THIS. YEAH.

10:55.611 --> 10:58.048
I KNOW HOW MUCH YOU'VE
BEEN WANTING TO GET
BACK IN THE ART WORLD.

10:58.135 --> 10:59.484
I HAVE.[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]

10:59.571 --> 11:01.399
HONEY,
WHAT DOES NEAL WANT?

11:01.486 --> 11:02.792
NOTHING. NOTHING.

11:02.879 --> 11:05.099
HE'S ON THIS...
TREASURE HUNT.

11:05.186 --> 11:06.796
A REAL TREASURE HUNT?

11:06.883 --> 11:10.408
YEAH. AN ECCENTRIC MILLIONAIRE
LEFT CODED WILLS TO HIS KIDS.

11:10.495 --> 11:12.672
[ LAUGHS ]
BORING.

11:12.759 --> 11:15.413
[ CELL PHONE BEEPS ]MM.

11:15.500 --> 11:16.980
IT'S FROM NEAL.

11:17.067 --> 11:18.721
IT IS?
YEAH.

11:18.808 --> 11:21.115
ALL RIGHT, HE SAID HE'S "FOUND
NOTHING OBVIOUS IN THE TIMES,

11:21.202 --> 11:23.334
BUT THE SUN WON'T SHINE
ON THE GNOMON FOR FOUR
MORE HOURS. THOUGHTS?"

11:26.033 --> 11:27.948
YOU JUST HAPPEN TO HAVE THE WILL
IN YOUR BACK POCKET?

11:28.035 --> 11:29.166
YEAH. "BE PREPARED."
EAGLE SCOUT.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.646
OF COURSE.

11:30.733 --> 11:33.127
ALL RIGHT, SEE,
THERE'S THIS LITTLE FLOWER

11:33.214 --> 11:34.911
RIGHT NEXT TO THE FIRST TIME
ON THE WILL.

11:34.998 --> 11:36.391
WHAT DO YOU THINK IT MEANS?

11:36.478 --> 11:39.176
WELL, IT'S A TULIP, WHICH
IS SYMBOLIC FOR REBIRTH...

11:39.263 --> 11:40.525
YEAH.
...SPRINGTIME, UM --

11:40.612 --> 11:42.397
THAT'S IT!

11:42.484 --> 11:44.704
THE ANGLE OF THE SUN IS GONNA
BE DIFFERENT IN THE SPRING

11:44.791 --> 11:46.444
RATHER THAN THE WINTER
OR THE SUMMER,

11:46.531 --> 11:50.100
SO THE SHADOW ON THE SUNDIAL
IS GONNA BE DIFFERENT.

11:50.187 --> 11:52.363
THEY COULD RE-CREATE IT
USING A COUPLE MIRRORS!

11:52.450 --> 11:54.844
BUT THAT DOESN'T MATTER.
DOESN'T MATTER.

11:54.931 --> 11:56.324
HONEY.
WHAT?

11:56.411 --> 11:57.891
DO YOU WANT TO GRAB SOME MIRRORS
AND GO PLAY WITH NEAL?

11:57.978 --> 11:59.196
YES!

11:59.283 --> 12:01.198
REMEMBER WHEN I SAID
THAT THINGS WERE GETTING

12:01.285 --> 12:02.939
BACK TO NORMAL
BETWEEN ME AND PETER?

12:03.026 --> 12:04.854
YEAH, THAT'S SWEET.
YOU KNOW, ONE SENTENCE IN,

12:04.941 --> 12:06.726
AND I ALREADY HATE
THIS CONVERSATION.

12:06.813 --> 12:09.076
WELL, THIS MORNING HE MET WITH
SOMEONE FROM D.C. ART CRIMES.

12:09.163 --> 12:10.686
SPECIALTY SUITS? WHY?

12:10.773 --> 12:12.427
I DON'T KNOW.
HE DIDN'T TELL ME.

12:12.514 --> 12:14.777
ART CRIMES ARE YOUR
FBI RAISON D'ETRE.

12:14.864 --> 12:16.344
YOU AREART CRIMES.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.172
THAT'S WHY
I'M LETTING YOU KNOW.

12:18.259 --> 12:19.564
I-IT COULD BE NOTHING.

12:19.651 --> 12:21.175
UNH! EVERYTHING POINTS
TO SOMETHING.

12:21.262 --> 12:22.654
WHO DID HE MEET WITH?

12:22.742 --> 12:25.266
NAME'S AGENT MATTHEWS.
SHE GOES BACK TO D.C. ON FRIDAY.

12:25.353 --> 12:26.963
OH, WELL, THAT GIVES US
PLENTY OF TIME.

12:27.050 --> 12:28.530
I ALREADY LINED UP A BUYER
FOR THE DEGAS, AND --

12:28.617 --> 12:29.836
Shh.

12:29.923 --> 12:31.925
ELIZABETH, PETER.

12:32.012 --> 12:34.275
COULDN'T STAY AWAY,
COULD YOU?

12:34.362 --> 12:36.930
WELL, NOT AFTER THAT FRANTIC
DISTRESS TEXT YOU LEFT MY WIFE.

12:37.017 --> 12:38.279
NEAL, MOZZIE.

12:38.366 --> 12:39.802
GOOD TO SEE YOU,
MRS. SUIT.
MM.

12:39.889 --> 12:42.239
I MAY HAVE SOLVED
THE SUNDIAL CODE.

12:42.326 --> 12:45.155
THERE'S A SYMBOL FOR EACH SEASON
NEXT TO THE TIME.

12:45.242 --> 12:47.201
USING THESE MIRRORS,

12:47.288 --> 12:50.987
WE CAN RE-CREATE
THE SEASONAL OFFSET.

12:51.074 --> 12:52.249
OOH, A SEXTANT.

12:52.336 --> 12:54.425
IT WAS A BIRTHDAY GIFT
FROM MY LOVELY WIFE --

12:54.512 --> 12:57.777
MWAH! -- THAT SHE SAID
I'D NEVER GET A CHANCE TO USE.

12:57.864 --> 12:59.604
HOW DID I NOT
FORESEE THIS?

12:59.691 --> 13:00.823
WHAT'S THE FIRST TIME?

13:00.910 --> 13:03.173
4:30.
Peter:
IN THE SPRING.

13:03.260 --> 13:05.001
YEAH, BUT NOT
THE GOVERNMENT-FORCED

13:05.088 --> 13:06.437
DAYLIGHT SAVINGS 4:30.

13:06.524 --> 13:08.135
THE REAL4:30.

13:08.222 --> 13:13.575
HON, IF YOU WOULD STAND --
RIGHT ABOUT HERE IS GOOD.

13:13.662 --> 13:15.795
Peter:
AND, MR. CONSPIRACY,

13:15.882 --> 13:20.364
IF YOU COULD STAND
RIGHT ABOUT HERE.

13:20.451 --> 13:22.584
AND NOT MOVE. GOOD.

13:25.500 --> 13:28.764
OKAY, HONEY, HOLD IT A LITTLE
HIGHER AND TO YOUR RIGHT.

13:30.897 --> 13:33.900
Peter: THAT'S IT. GOOD.
SWIVEL IT TOWARDS...

13:35.118 --> 13:36.163
ALL RIGHT, HONEY.

13:36.250 --> 13:37.468
THAT'S IT.

13:37.555 --> 13:39.383
RIGHT THERE.

13:39.470 --> 13:40.558
IT'S POINTING
TO THE LETTER "B."

13:40.645 --> 13:42.517
WE'RE ONTO SOMETHING.

13:42.604 --> 13:44.780
WHAT'S THE NEXT LETTER?

13:44.867 --> 13:46.434
2:00, AND THE SYMBOL
IS THE SUN.

13:46.521 --> 13:47.783
2:00 IN THE SUMMER.
YEAH.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.524
Peter: MOZZIE...

13:49.611 --> 13:54.311
TWO STEPS TO YOUR LEFT.

13:54.398 --> 13:56.923
HOLD YOUR ARMS UP
AS HIGH AS YOU CAN.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.489
IS THAT A SHORT JOKE?

13:58.576 --> 13:59.534
IT IS NOW.

13:59.621 --> 14:01.275
AND TO YOUR RIGHT.

14:01.362 --> 14:03.581
HONEY, SWIVEL LEFT
JUST A LITTLE BIT MORE.

14:03.668 --> 14:07.107
ALMOST THERE. THAT'S IT.
RIGHT THERE.

14:07.194 --> 14:08.499
"S."

14:09.761 --> 14:12.939
ALL RIGHT,
WHAT'S THE NEXT TIME?

14:13.026 --> 14:16.420
OKAY.
MOZZIE, UH, TWO STEPS BACK.

14:16.507 --> 14:19.206
THAT'S -- RIGHT THERE.
AND HOLD THE MIRROR LOWER.

14:19.293 --> 14:22.122
AND LOWER. LOWER.

14:22.209 --> 14:23.558
LOWER.

14:23.645 --> 14:25.908
SWIVEL IT, HONEY.
THAT'S IT. RIGHT THERE.

14:25.995 --> 14:26.953
AND TO YOUR RIGHT.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.432
THERE YOU GO.
GOOD. LOWER.

14:28.519 --> 14:30.130
RIGHT THERE.

14:30.217 --> 14:31.435
"H."

14:31.522 --> 14:33.220
B.S.H.
DOES THAT MEAN
ANYTHING TO YOU?

14:33.307 --> 14:34.743
NO.

14:34.830 --> 14:39.052
THREE-LETTER ACRONYMS
ARE YOUR SPECIALTY, SUIT.

14:39.139 --> 14:41.315
BACK TO
THE DRAWING BOARD?Peter: HUH.

14:41.402 --> 14:43.534
[ CELL PHONE RINGING ]

14:43.621 --> 14:46.059
THANKS, HONEY.
YEAH.

14:46.146 --> 14:48.496
[ BEEP ]YEAH, JONES?

14:48.583 --> 14:50.498
I JUST GOT OFF THE PHONE
WITH JAMES ROLAND.

14:50.585 --> 14:51.978
What's going on?

14:52.065 --> 14:53.980
THE TREASURE HUNT JUST TURNED
INTO A KIDNAPPING.

14:54.067 --> 14:57.722
Someone's taken
Savannah.

14:57.809 --> 14:59.986
[ BEEPING ]

15:07.167 --> 15:09.082
Diana: CYBER CRIMES
AND THE KIDNAPPING SQUAD

15:09.169 --> 15:11.693
ARE PUTTING TOGETHER A COMMAND
CENTER AT ROLAND'S ESTATE.

15:11.780 --> 15:14.217
JAMES IS THERE WITH THEM,
AND WE'VE BEEN TALKING TO
JOSH IN THE INTERVIEW ROOM.

15:14.304 --> 15:15.740
THE RANSOM IS DUE IN LESS
THAN SIX HOURS.

15:15.827 --> 15:17.220
HOW ARE WE COMMUNICATING
WITH THE KIDNAPPER?

15:17.307 --> 15:19.440
WEBSITE.

15:19.527 --> 15:21.964
Peter: THE DOMAIN IS ACTUALLY
KidnappedSavannah.com?

15:22.051 --> 15:23.357
THAT TAKES
SOME PREMEDITATION.

15:23.444 --> 15:25.707
JAMES GOT A CALL
TO CHECK THIS U.R.L.

15:25.794 --> 15:28.188
IT'S STREAMING A LIVE FEED,
BUT IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
SHE'S AWARE OF THE CAMERA.

15:28.275 --> 15:29.580
Neal:
SHE'S IN GOOD SPIRITS.

15:29.667 --> 15:31.321
SO MOST LIKELY
SHE KNOWS HER KIDNAPPER.

15:31.408 --> 15:32.453
WHAT ARE THE DEMANDS?

15:32.540 --> 15:33.410
IT'S ON THE WEBSITE.

15:35.586 --> 15:37.327
A "DEMAND" TAB.
LOOK AT THAT.

15:37.414 --> 15:38.981
WELCOME
TO THE 21st CENTURY.

15:39.068 --> 15:40.417
GUY'S DEFINITELY
TECH-SAVVY.

15:40.504 --> 15:42.158
THE SITE IS A LABYRINTH
OF CLOUD DATA

15:42.245 --> 15:44.247
THAT THEY CAN'T TRACE BEYOND
A FIREWALL IN THE UKRAINE.

15:44.334 --> 15:45.466
[ BEEP ]

15:45.553 --> 15:46.989
Diana: $6.4 MILLION.

15:47.076 --> 15:48.382
LET ME SEE JAMES' WILL.

15:52.429 --> 15:55.867
THAT'S THE EXACT AMOUNT
ROLAND LEFT TO HIM IN CASH.

15:55.955 --> 15:56.956
KIDNAPPER'S SEEN
THIS WILL.

15:58.392 --> 15:59.654
YEAH.

15:59.741 --> 16:01.525
THIS IS PERSONAL.

16:03.136 --> 16:05.790
ALMOST HALF OF ALL KIDNAPPINGS
ARE BY A RELATIVE.

16:05.877 --> 16:08.880
LOOK, JAMES AND I MAY HAVE
OUR DIFFERENCES,

16:08.968 --> 16:12.101
BUT NOBODY IN OUR FAMILY WOULD
EVER DO ANYTHING TO HURT HER.

16:12.188 --> 16:14.886
HONESTLY, SAVANNAH'S THE ONLY
REASON WE STILL EVEN SPEAK.

16:16.584 --> 16:19.500
BUT IF WE FIND THE REAL WILL,
WE CAN PAY THE RANSOM.

16:19.587 --> 16:21.458
YOU SAID THIS IS A MAP?MM-HMM.

16:21.545 --> 16:23.069
ALL RIGHT.

16:23.156 --> 16:25.071
JAMES CAN STAY BACK AT THE
HOUSE. I'M GONNA FOLLOW IT.

16:25.158 --> 16:26.986
UH, THE TRUTH IS,
I ALREADY TOOK THE INITIATIVE

16:27.073 --> 16:28.857
AND WENT
TO THE SUNDIAL.YOU WHAT?

16:28.944 --> 16:31.381
IT GAVE US
THE LETTERS B.S.H.

16:31.468 --> 16:34.167
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT STANDS FOR?

16:34.254 --> 16:35.820
YEAH, THAT WAS DAD'S
FAVORITE ACRONYM.

16:35.907 --> 16:37.387
IT MEANS
"BIG SKY HUNTING."

16:37.474 --> 16:38.867
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

16:38.954 --> 16:40.608
IT MEANT HE WAS TAKING US
TO THE PLANETARIUM,

16:40.695 --> 16:42.175
OR, AS HE WOULD PUT IT,

16:42.262 --> 16:44.003
THE ONLY PLACE TO SEE STARS
IN MANHATTAN.

16:44.090 --> 16:45.961
THAT'S WHERE I'M GOING.Peter: NO. JOSH.

16:46.048 --> 16:47.615
THESE FIRST FEW HOURS
ARE CRITICAL

16:47.702 --> 16:49.530
TO FIGURING OUT
WHO TOOK SAVANNAH.

16:49.617 --> 16:52.881
THE BEST THING THAT YOU CAN DO
IS TO WORK WITH YOUR BROTHER

16:52.968 --> 16:55.797
TO HELP US BUILD
A SUSPECT PROFILE.

16:59.714 --> 17:02.630
ALL RIGHT, FINE, BUT I WANT
TO KNOW WHERE THIS LEADS.

17:02.717 --> 17:04.284
WILL YOU FOLLOW
THIS MAP FOR ME?

17:04.371 --> 17:06.329
SURE THING.PROMISE ME.

17:06.416 --> 17:08.462
WE'LL KEEP YOU POSTED
EVERY STEP OF THE WAY.

17:10.072 --> 17:11.247
THANK YOU.

17:23.607 --> 17:26.088
Neal: WELL, THIS IS ONE WAY TO
GET TO GO ON A TREASURE HUNT.

17:26.175 --> 17:28.090
Peter: I'M NOT WILD
ABOUT JAMES PAYING RANSOM,

17:28.177 --> 17:30.310
BUT WE NEED HIM WORKING WITH US
TO FIND HIS DAUGHTER.

17:30.397 --> 17:32.573
I WAS STARTING TO THINK
YOU DIDN'T TRUST MOZZIE AND I

17:32.660 --> 17:34.314
TO GO AFTER THIS UNSUPERVISED.THAT TOO.

17:34.401 --> 17:36.664
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

17:36.751 --> 17:38.405
OH. SPECIAL AGENT BURKE.Peter: MM.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.537
AH. UH, I'M FELIX.

17:40.624 --> 17:42.148
WELL, THIS IS
THE FIRST TIME

17:42.235 --> 17:43.888
A G-MAN HAS COME
TO THE PLANETARIUM

17:43.975 --> 17:45.194
ON OFFICIAL BUSINESS.

17:47.805 --> 17:50.808
UH, YOU HAD INQUIRED
ABOUT NATHANIEL ROLAND.

17:50.895 --> 17:52.984
YES. WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
HE WAS HERE?

17:53.072 --> 17:54.160
2:00 P.M.
ON DECEMBER 3rd.

17:56.075 --> 17:59.730
OH, IT WAS A VERY, UH, BIG DEAL
WHEN MR. ROLAND POPPED BY.

17:59.817 --> 18:01.776
USUALLY MEANT SOMEONE
WAS GETTING A NEW TELESCOPE.

18:03.038 --> 18:05.562
HUH.
I KNOW HE SIGNED IN.

18:05.649 --> 18:06.563
MAY I?

18:06.650 --> 18:08.870
THANK YOU.

18:10.654 --> 18:13.092
HE DID SIGN IN,
JUST NOT UNDER ROLAND.

18:13.179 --> 18:14.223
"TYCHO BRAHE."

18:14.310 --> 18:15.442
YEAH.
LOOK AT THAT REMARK.

18:15.529 --> 18:17.661
"HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO ME"?

18:17.748 --> 18:19.924
DECEMBER 14, 1546.

18:20.011 --> 18:22.318
UH, TYCHO BRAHE.

18:22.405 --> 18:23.885
THAT'S HIS BIRTHDAY.

18:23.972 --> 18:27.497
FELIX, WOULD YOU MIND
FIRING UP THE PROJECTOR?

18:27.584 --> 18:30.413
IT'S TIME TO GO
BIG SKY HUNTING.

18:30.500 --> 18:32.328
[ WHIRRING ]

18:48.823 --> 18:50.477
Felix:
THIS IS OUR SKY TODAY.

18:50.564 --> 18:54.089
NOW LET ME BRING YOU
BACK TO TYCHO'S BIRTHDAY.

19:00.922 --> 19:03.664
AND HERE WE ARE IN 1592.

19:03.751 --> 19:06.275
Peter: WE KNOW THE TIME AND DATE
TO LOOK AT THE STARS.

19:06.362 --> 19:10.584
NOW WE JUST NEED TO FIGURE OUT
WHERE IN THE SKY.

19:10.671 --> 19:12.847
IN HIS WILL, ROLAND TALKS
ABOUT BIG SKY HUNTING

19:12.934 --> 19:14.544
WITH HIS FAVORITE TWINS.

19:14.631 --> 19:16.590
JOSH AND JAMES
AREN'T TWINS.

19:16.677 --> 19:18.809
NO.
THEY'RE A YEAR APART.

19:18.896 --> 19:21.247
MAYBE HE WAS TALKING ABOUT
THE TWINS IN THE SKY.

19:21.334 --> 19:24.163
FELIX, WHERE ARE
THE GEMINI TWINS?

19:30.081 --> 19:31.518
I ONLY SEE ONE BROTHER.

19:31.605 --> 19:33.215
WELL, THEY'RE SPLIT
ON THE HORIZON --

19:33.302 --> 19:34.695
ONE ABOVE, ONE BELOW.

19:34.782 --> 19:38.002
TYCHO HAD A TWIN WHO DIED
SHORTLY AFTER HE WAS BORN.

19:38.089 --> 19:40.962
INTERESTINGLY, BRAHE WROTE
A LETTER TO HIS DECEASED TWIN

19:41.049 --> 19:42.833
IN HIS FIRST PUBLISHED WORK.

19:42.920 --> 19:45.009
THAT'S GOT TO BE IT.

19:45.096 --> 19:46.446
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT WAS IN THE LETTER?

19:46.533 --> 19:47.621
NO.

19:48.883 --> 19:50.493
UH, BUT I CAN SHOW IT
TO YOU.

19:50.580 --> 19:54.671
WE HAVE THE FIRST PRINTED COPY
OF BRAHE'S COLLECTED WORKS.

19:54.758 --> 19:56.978
IT'S ON DISPLAY
IN THE NORTH GALLERY.

19:57.065 --> 20:00.024
LET ME GUESS --
A GENEROUS DONATION FROM...NATHANIEL ROLAND?

20:00.111 --> 20:02.157
PRECISELY.

20:06.335 --> 20:09.338
TYCHO BRAHE'S ORIGINAL NOTES
ON "DE NOVA STELLA."

20:09.425 --> 20:12.994
THE LETTER HE WROTE
TO HIS BROTHER IS ON PAGE 273.

20:17.172 --> 20:19.043
WOULD YOU MIND
TURNING TO THAT PAGE?

20:19.130 --> 20:21.089
WELL,
THAT WOULD BE IMPOSSIBLE.

20:21.176 --> 20:22.656
MR. ROLAND LEFT THE BOOK

20:22.743 --> 20:24.397
WITH VERY SPECIFIC
INSTRUCTION.

20:24.484 --> 20:25.789
OF COURSE HE DID.

20:25.876 --> 20:28.401
AH.

20:28.488 --> 20:30.316
"THE MECHANICAL ARM TURNS
ONE PAGE EVERY HOUR

20:30.403 --> 20:31.665
"UNTIL IT REACHES THE END.

20:31.752 --> 20:33.449
THEN THE PROCESS REVERSES."

20:33.536 --> 20:35.321
Felix:
THIS IS HALF-INCH GLASS.

20:35.408 --> 20:36.974
PRESSURE, TEMPERATURE,
AND HUMIDITY ARE CONTROLLED

20:37.061 --> 20:38.324
TO PRESERVE THE PAPER.

20:38.411 --> 20:40.456
IT CANNOT BE TAMPERED WITH
IN ANY WAY.

20:40.543 --> 20:42.284
LISTEN TO ME, FELIX.

20:42.371 --> 20:44.982
THIS BOOK MAY HAVE IMPLICATIONS
IN A KIDNAPPING.

20:45.069 --> 20:46.636
OH.

20:46.723 --> 20:48.595
OH, I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT,
BUT...

20:48.682 --> 20:50.249
BUT YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

20:50.336 --> 20:54.209
I WISH I COULD HELP YOU,
BUT MY HANDS ARE TIED.

20:54.296 --> 20:56.342
[ WHIRRING ]

20:56.429 --> 20:58.605
YOU COULD COME BACK
IN A FEW DAYS.

21:01.303 --> 21:03.044
Peter: RIGHT. OKAY.
THANKS, DIANA.

21:03.131 --> 21:04.654
Neal:
WHAT'S GOING ON?

21:04.741 --> 21:05.916
SHE'S GOT A SOLID LEAD.

21:06.003 --> 21:07.570
I'M MEETING HER
BACK AT THE BUREAU.

21:07.657 --> 21:10.530
WHAT ABOUT THE BOOK? WE TOLD
JAMES WE'D SEE THIS THROUGH.

21:10.617 --> 21:13.707
I SAID I'MMEETING HER
BACK AT THE FBI, NOT YOU.

21:13.794 --> 21:16.057
ARE YOU SAYING YOU TRUST ME
ENOUGH TO CONTINUE WITHOUT YOU?

21:16.144 --> 21:17.928
NEAL, WE GOT TO
GET SAVANNAH BACK.

21:18.015 --> 21:21.541
WITH THAT,
I TRUST YOU COMPLETELY.

21:27.590 --> 21:30.811
Mozzie: WE JUST NEED TO FLIP
A FEW PAGES OF A BOOK.

21:30.898 --> 21:33.944
THAT SOUNDS SIMPLE ENOUGH.
SEEMS COMPLETELY POSSIBLE.

21:34.031 --> 21:35.859
YET IF I'M READING THIS
CORRECTLY...

21:35.946 --> 21:37.339
IT'S COMPLETELY IMPOSSIBLE.

21:37.426 --> 21:38.732
THIS IS A CENTURIES-OLD BOOK

21:38.819 --> 21:40.386
WRITTEN TO A MAN'S
DEAD TWIN BROTHER,

21:40.473 --> 21:41.996
DONATED BY
AN EQUALLY ECCENTRIC,

21:42.083 --> 21:43.911
RECENTLY DECEASED
MODERN-DAY HOWARD HUGHES

21:43.998 --> 21:45.652
AS PART OF A POSTHUMOUS
TREASURE HUNT.

21:45.739 --> 21:47.393
THERE'S NOTHING SIMPLE
ABOUT THIS ONE.

21:47.480 --> 21:50.657
HOW ABOUT...
A CANNONBALL?

21:50.744 --> 21:52.093
NO.
THAT'S TOO MANY PEOPLE.

21:52.180 --> 21:53.790
THIS PLACE IS NEARLY EMPTY
DURING THE DAY.

21:53.877 --> 21:55.139
THEY ONLY HAVE
TWO EMPLOYEES.

21:56.445 --> 21:58.186
WE COULD DO THE LAZY SUSAN.

21:58.273 --> 21:59.666
I LIKE WHAT YOU'RE THINKING,

21:59.753 --> 22:01.885
BUT I DON'T WANT THE SPRINKLER
SYSTEM RUNNING,

22:01.972 --> 22:04.801
NOT WHEN WE MIGHT HAVE TO
EXPOSE THE MANUSCRIPT.

22:04.888 --> 22:08.936
THIS USES
AN EAGLE-ONE ALARM SYSTEM.

22:10.677 --> 22:13.419
SO DOES THE REST
OF THE PLANETARIUM.

22:13.506 --> 22:15.464
THAT MEANS THERE'S
A SINGLE ACCESS CODE

22:15.551 --> 22:18.162
FOR EVERY KEYPAD
IN THE WHOLE PLACE.

22:18.249 --> 22:19.425
BLIND MAN'S BLUFF.

22:19.512 --> 22:21.688
THAT COULD WORK.

22:21.775 --> 22:22.689
WE'RE GONNA NEED A DOG.

22:22.776 --> 22:24.081
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

22:24.168 --> 22:27.476
SATCHMO, DON'T WORRY.
I'VE GOT THE DOOR.

22:27.563 --> 22:29.739
YOU JUST STAY RIGHT THERE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:29.826 --> 22:32.481
MOZZIE. NEAL. UM...

22:32.568 --> 22:34.091
WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
DOING HERE?

22:34.178 --> 22:35.919
IS SATCHMO FREE
THIS AFTERNOON?

22:47.017 --> 22:49.063
Diana: WE'VE ZEROED IN
ON A MAN NAMED BRETT GELLES.

22:49.150 --> 22:51.500
HE COMES BY EVERY YEAR TO UPDATE
ROLAND'S SECURITY SYSTEM.

22:51.587 --> 22:53.850
TECH-SAVVY, HAS A RELATIONSHIP
WITH SAVANNAH.

22:53.937 --> 22:55.243
TELLS HER HE'S THE GUY
WHO KEEPS HER SAFE.

22:55.330 --> 22:56.331
Jones: WE DID
A FINANCIAL WORK-UP.

22:56.418 --> 22:57.767
HIS BUSINESS
IS ALL DRIED UP.

22:57.854 --> 22:59.378
Peter:
SERIOUS CREDIT PROBLEMS.

22:59.465 --> 23:01.292
HAVE WE LOCATED HIM?HE'S NOT AT HOME.

23:01.380 --> 23:03.207
WE HAVE A TEAM SEARCHING HIS
PLACE NOW. NO SIGN OF ANYTHING.

23:03.294 --> 23:04.600
THAT'S NOT HIS HOME.

23:04.687 --> 23:06.385
HE DOESN'T HAVE AN OFFICE.

23:06.472 --> 23:07.908
WHERE IS HE KEEPING HER?

23:07.995 --> 23:09.431
SOMEWHERE SHE FEELS
COMFORTABLE.

23:09.518 --> 23:11.433
AND HE FEELS SECURE ENOUGH
TO LEAVE HER ALONE.

23:11.520 --> 23:12.434
WHAT ABOUT A HOTEL?

23:12.521 --> 23:15.829
NO. TOO CONSPICUOUS.

23:15.916 --> 23:18.962
GET ME A LIST OF ALL THE PLACES
HE'S DONE SECURITY ON.

23:19.049 --> 23:21.356
AH, YOU THINK HE'S CAMPING OUT
AT ONE OF HIS CLIENTS' HOMES.

23:21.443 --> 23:24.620
FIND OUT IF ANY OF THEM
ARE OUT OF TOWN.

23:24.707 --> 23:27.754
[ BEEPING ]

23:27.841 --> 23:29.843
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:59.263 --> 24:00.569
YOU'RE ON.[ SATCHMO WHIMPERS ]

24:02.092 --> 24:03.703
HOO-AH!

24:08.925 --> 24:11.058
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
UNFORTUNATELY,

24:11.145 --> 24:13.974
THE TYCHO BRAHE EXHIBIT'S
GONNA BE CLOSED FOR THE
REST OF THE AFTERNOON.

24:14.061 --> 24:17.020
WE APOLOGIZE FOR
ANY INCONVENIENCE
THIS MAY CAUSE YOU.

24:17.107 --> 24:19.849
UH, IF YOU'D LIKE, OUR NEXT
SCREENING OF "ACROSS THE GALAXY"

24:19.936 --> 24:21.634
STARTS IN OUR THEATER
IN FIVE MINUTES.

24:21.721 --> 24:23.505
YOU DON'T WANT TO MISS IT.
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

24:23.592 --> 24:26.160
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

24:32.209 --> 24:35.561
I LIKE THE IDEAOF STARS.

24:40.566 --> 24:41.828
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:41.915 --> 24:43.960
GO, SATCHMO. GO.

24:45.875 --> 24:48.443
HELP!
I-I-I LOST MY GUIDE DOG!

24:48.530 --> 24:50.793
HELP --UH, HE'S IN MY OFFICE.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.316
HAS ANYONE SEEN --
I LOST MY DOG.

24:52.403 --> 24:54.144
SIR, HE'S IN MY OFFICE.

24:54.231 --> 24:55.232
WHO ARE YOU?

24:55.319 --> 24:56.886
I'M FELIX, THE DOCENT.

24:56.973 --> 24:58.671
I'M SO SORRY, FELIX.

24:58.758 --> 25:00.368
I-I DON'T KNOW
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO HIM.

25:00.455 --> 25:01.587
THESE THINGS HAPPEN.

25:01.674 --> 25:02.631
YES, THEY CERTAINLY DO.

25:02.718 --> 25:04.111
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

25:04.198 --> 25:05.808
[ BEEP ]

25:11.640 --> 25:12.772
[ DOOR OPENS ]COME IN.

25:19.082 --> 25:20.344
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES, BEEPS ]

25:28.439 --> 25:30.311
ALL RIGHT.

25:38.580 --> 25:41.017
[ BEEPING ]

25:50.723 --> 25:52.638
[ ELECTRICITY CRACKLES ]

25:54.291 --> 25:56.467
[ WHIRRING ]

25:59.645 --> 26:01.385
WHAT DO WE HAVE?

26:01.472 --> 26:04.084
WE HAVE GELLES HAVING INSTALLED
22 HOME-SECURITY SYSTEMS.

26:04.171 --> 26:05.825
FOUR OF THOSE HOMEOWNERS
ARE ON VACATION.

26:05.912 --> 26:07.087
SHOULD WE MOVE IN
ON THEM?

26:07.174 --> 26:08.828
VERY CAREFULLY.

26:08.915 --> 26:10.699
SEND A TEAM
TO SIT ON THESE PLACES.

26:10.786 --> 26:12.179
LOOK, HE'S NOT HURTING HER,

26:12.266 --> 26:14.616
SO I DON'T WANT A FORCE THIS
INTO A HOSTAGE SITUATION.

26:14.703 --> 26:16.662
BUT LET ME KNOW IF THERE'S
SO MUCH AS A FLICKER INSIDE.

26:18.359 --> 26:20.666
SATCHMO, GO SIT.

26:20.753 --> 26:22.189
SIT. GOOD BOY.

26:22.276 --> 26:25.061
SO, D.C. ART CRIMES --
ANY NEW INFO?

26:25.148 --> 26:26.759
THAT ROOKIE AGENT'S IN TOWN
TILL TOMORROW.

26:26.846 --> 26:28.238
SHE DOESN'T KNOW WHO I AM.

26:28.325 --> 26:30.371
[ GASPS ]
THE OLD TRAVELING SALESMAN.

26:30.458 --> 26:32.373
YEAH. GOOD IDEA.[ WHIRRING ]

26:32.460 --> 26:34.723
ALL RIGHT.
HOW WE LOOKING UP THERE?

26:34.810 --> 26:36.769
[ WHIRRING ]

26:36.856 --> 26:38.597
Mozzie: YOU MISSED IT.

26:38.684 --> 26:40.642
WE NEED PAGE 273.

26:40.729 --> 26:42.688
YEAH. I KNOW.
IT'S THE FIRST TIME IT SKIPPED.

26:42.775 --> 26:44.298
CAN YOU MAKE IT REVERSE?HOLD ON.

26:44.385 --> 26:47.040
[ WHIRRING ]

26:47.127 --> 26:49.042
OKAY, SERIOUSLY?

26:49.129 --> 26:50.521
WHAT, YOU WANT TO COME DOWN
AND GIVE IT A GO, BOB VILA?

26:50.609 --> 26:51.610
[ CELL PHONE RINGS ]BRING IT.

26:51.697 --> 26:53.220
OH, GOOD NEWS.
WHAT?

26:53.307 --> 26:55.135
UH, I'M GONNA FENCE
THE DEGAS TONIGHT.

26:55.222 --> 26:56.702
YEAH.
THAT'S GREAT NEWS, MOZ.

26:56.789 --> 26:58.138
BUT CAN WE HANDLE THE BOOK,
PLEASE? WE DON'T HAVE TIME.

26:58.225 --> 26:59.487
OH.

26:59.574 --> 27:01.184
YEAH.WE NEED TO CUT A HOLE.

27:01.271 --> 27:02.795
YEAH.

27:02.882 --> 27:05.406
JUST BIG ENOUGH FOR THE POINTER
TO TURN THE PAGE.

27:05.493 --> 27:06.886
AND WE CAN SEAL IT
WITH A POLYMER FILAMENT.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.585
PLEASE TELL ME YOU BROUGHT
A POLYMER FILAMENT.

27:11.717 --> 27:12.587
MY FAVORITE BRAND.

27:14.894 --> 27:16.983
ARE YOU READY?
YEP.

27:17.070 --> 27:18.680
IF THIS DOESN'T WORK,
WE BLAME THE DOG.

27:18.767 --> 27:19.986
[ SATCHMO WHINES ]

27:20.073 --> 27:22.205
[ TOOL WHIRRING ]

27:31.780 --> 27:34.130
[ AIR HISSING ]

27:44.619 --> 27:45.881
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

27:49.842 --> 27:51.278
[ SATCHMO WHINES ]BAD DOG!

28:02.898 --> 28:04.595
NEAL, SOMEHOW YOU MANAGED
TO MAKE MY DOG

28:04.683 --> 28:06.249
AN ACCOMPLICE TO ROBBERY.

28:06.336 --> 28:07.598
[ SATCHMO WHIMPERS ]

28:07.686 --> 28:09.339
ELIZABETH SAID I'D BEAR
THE BRUNT OF THIS.

28:09.426 --> 28:11.298
YOU KNOW,
I GIVE YOU AN INCH, AND --

28:11.385 --> 28:12.734
NOW IT'S LIGHT READING.

28:12.821 --> 28:14.214
TOO SOON.

28:14.301 --> 28:16.651
THE PLANETARIUM
INTENDS TO PROSECUTE.

28:16.738 --> 28:18.827
THIS BOOK IS A FORGERY.

28:18.914 --> 28:20.394
BRAHE LIVED ON AN ISLAND.

28:20.481 --> 28:22.788
HE RAN HIS OWN PAPER MILL,
PRIMARILY FROM TULIP-TREE STOCK,

28:22.875 --> 28:24.441
WHICH HAS A VERY LOW
ACETIC CONTENT.

28:24.528 --> 28:26.052
LOOK, THE REAL MANUSCRIPT
COULD BE LEFT

28:26.139 --> 28:28.489
IN A TURKISH BATHHOUSE
WITHOUT RISK OF HARM.

28:28.576 --> 28:31.100
THE ONE FROM THE PLANETARIUM
TURNED INTO A SHRINKY DINK
THE SECOND IT HIT THE AIR.

28:31.187 --> 28:33.276
SO ROLAND INTENDEDFOR YOU
TO DESTROY THIS BOOK.

28:33.363 --> 28:34.495
YES.

28:34.582 --> 28:36.062
WHEW.

28:36.149 --> 28:37.846
WHAT?
THESE SYMBOLS.

28:37.933 --> 28:40.283
I'VE SEEN THEM BEFORE --
ON SAVANNAH'S ANKLET...

28:40.370 --> 28:42.895
WHICH WAS GIVEN TO HER
BY HER GRANDFATHER.

28:42.982 --> 28:44.070
SO SAVANNAH'S
THE NEXT CLUE.
MM-HMM.

28:44.157 --> 28:45.898
IS IT TOO SOON TO SAY
"I TOLD YOU SO"?

28:45.985 --> 28:47.421
YES.
ALL RIGHT.[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

28:47.508 --> 28:49.466
CON ED IS REPORTING
AN INCREASE IN POWER USAGE

28:49.553 --> 28:51.077
AT THE HOME ON 68th.

28:51.164 --> 28:52.818
OKAY. I'M GOING TO 68th.

28:52.905 --> 28:54.645
DIANA, I WANT YOU
TO RUN POINT HERE.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.865
JONES, YOU STAY WITH JAMES
AND JOSH AT COMMAND CENTER.

28:56.952 --> 29:01.391
GELLES HAS TO MAKE CONTACT SOON
SO WE CAN SET UP THE DROP.

29:01.478 --> 29:03.698
IF HE'S IN THE HOUSE WITH HER,
THIS COULD GET UGLY.

29:03.785 --> 29:05.569
WHAT IF I COULD LURE HIM
OUT OF THE HOUSE?

29:05.656 --> 29:07.876
HOW?
TELL HIM JAMES
DOESN'T HAVE THE MONEY.

29:07.963 --> 29:09.399
IT'S ALL TIED UP
IN THE TREASURE HUNT.

29:09.486 --> 29:11.575
THE ONLY WAY
HE GETS HIS RANSOM

29:11.662 --> 29:13.447
IS TO GIVE US
SAVANNAH'S ANKLET.

29:13.534 --> 29:15.057
GIVE ME TWO MINUTES
ON THE PHONE WITH HIM.

29:15.144 --> 29:17.146
OKAY. LET'S DO IT.

29:17.233 --> 29:18.234
ALL RIGHT.

29:23.283 --> 29:24.458
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

29:24.545 --> 29:26.373
[ BEEPING ]

29:30.420 --> 29:32.205
[ SIGHS ]

29:32.292 --> 29:35.251
[ BEEP ]

29:35.338 --> 29:36.775
Neal: HELLO?GELLES: Put James on.

29:36.862 --> 29:38.167
NO.

29:38.254 --> 29:40.691
Damn it.
I said no cops.

29:40.779 --> 29:43.433
I AM THE FARTHEST THING FROM
A COP THAT YOU CAN IMAGINE.

29:43.520 --> 29:46.045
I'M JAMES ROLAND'S
IN-HOUSE COUNCIL.

29:46.132 --> 29:48.003
I'M HERE TO ENSURE THAT EVERYONE
GETS WHAT THEY WANT.

29:50.092 --> 29:51.528
I'M LISTENING.

29:51.615 --> 29:53.704
SAVANNAH WAS WEARING
AN ANKLE BRACELET.

29:53.792 --> 29:56.185
IT'S THE KEY TO UNLOCKING
MR. ROLAND'S FORTUNE.

29:56.272 --> 29:58.013
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

29:58.100 --> 30:01.060
WELL, MR. ROLAND LEFT BEHIND
A RATHER UNORTHODOX WILL.

30:01.147 --> 30:02.713
IT'S A GAME, AND NOW WE ALL
HAVE TO PLAY ALONG.

30:04.324 --> 30:06.239
I'M NOT BRINGING SAVANNAH
TO YOU.

30:08.110 --> 30:09.329
THEN JUST THE BRACELET.

30:09.416 --> 30:12.462
What, y-you think
I'm an idiot?

30:12.549 --> 30:14.377
COME ON, BRETT.

30:14.464 --> 30:17.641
We know who you are.

30:17.728 --> 30:18.991
AND WE KNOW
FROM YOUR VIDEO FEED

30:19.078 --> 30:20.557
THAT YOU DON'T WANT
TO HURT SAVANNAH.

30:20.644 --> 30:24.300
The brothers just want to settle
this quickly and quietly.

30:24.387 --> 30:26.085
YOU KNOW HOW ECCENTRIC
ROLAND WAS.

30:26.172 --> 30:27.956
Bring us her anklet,
and you'll get your money.

30:28.043 --> 30:29.566
[ BEEP ]

30:29.653 --> 30:31.481
[ Dial tone ]

30:31.568 --> 30:32.743
[ BEEP ]
[ SIGHS ]

30:32.831 --> 30:35.268
HE HUNG UP?
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

30:35.355 --> 30:36.791
WE CAUGHT HIM OFF GUARD,
ALL RIGHT?

30:36.878 --> 30:38.227
HE JUST NEEDS TO FORMULATE
A NEW PLAN.

30:38.314 --> 30:39.925
[ BEEPING ]

30:41.796 --> 30:44.668
[ BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

30:44.755 --> 30:45.974
THE CLOCK
JUST WENT TO ZERO.

30:46.061 --> 30:47.933
OHH! DAMN IT!

30:48.020 --> 30:50.283
[ JAMES EXHALES SHARPLY ]

30:53.242 --> 30:55.114
[ BREATHING SHARPLY ]

31:11.304 --> 31:13.262
PETER,
DID YOU HEAR THE CALL?

31:13.349 --> 31:15.308
COPY. NO MOVEMENT
AT TARGET ONE.

31:17.397 --> 31:19.921
TEAM THREE?

31:20.008 --> 31:22.184
Diana: PETER, HE MAY NOT BE
AT ANY OF THESE LOCATIONS.

31:22.271 --> 31:24.186
CON ED GOT BACK TO US.
THE POWER BLIP BEFORE

31:24.273 --> 31:25.971
WAS CAUSED BY
THE AIR-CONDITIONING UNIT.

31:26.058 --> 31:27.363
NOBODY'S IN THAT HOME.

31:27.450 --> 31:29.191
You're definitely
in the wrong place.

31:29.278 --> 31:33.326
OKAY. I WANT YOU TO RECHECK
EVERY INCH OF GELLES' HOME.

31:33.413 --> 31:36.242
I WANT PHONE RECORDS, RECEIPTS,
ANYTHING THAT TELLS US

31:36.329 --> 31:37.808
WHERE HE'S BEEN
IN THE LAST COUPLE MONTHS.

31:37.896 --> 31:38.897
Copy that.

31:40.246 --> 31:42.030
WHERE ARE YOU, GELLES?

31:42.117 --> 31:44.598
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

31:59.134 --> 32:00.788
GELLES?

32:00.875 --> 32:03.095
YOU KNOW WHO I AM.
WHAT'S THE POINT IN HIDING?

32:03.182 --> 32:05.140
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

32:05.227 --> 32:06.533
Jones:
EASY! EASY! EASY.

32:07.882 --> 32:10.276
DADDY, WHERE ARE YOU?

32:10.363 --> 32:11.886
[ GRUNTS ] UNCLE JOSH?

32:11.973 --> 32:14.671
HELP ME!SEE?

32:14.758 --> 32:16.064
NOW, ANYTHING HAPPENS TO ME,

32:16.151 --> 32:19.285
ANYBODY FOLLOWS ME
WHEN I LEAVE,

32:19.372 --> 32:20.982
AND YOU CAN ALL SIT AROUND
AND WATCH HER DIE.

32:21.069 --> 32:23.332
I'M THE ONLY ONE
THAT KNOWS WHERE SHE IS,

32:23.419 --> 32:25.508
AND I'M NOT TELLING
TILL I GET MY MONEY.

32:25.595 --> 32:28.642
FBI AGENTS -- OUT. NOW.

32:28.729 --> 32:31.950
NOW! GO.

32:34.082 --> 32:35.649
LET'S CLEAR OUT.

32:35.736 --> 32:37.564
LET'S GO!

32:44.179 --> 32:45.789
I STAY.

32:45.876 --> 32:47.226
GUY ON THE PHONE.

32:47.313 --> 32:48.183
I AM.

32:49.358 --> 32:51.273
HERE.

32:51.360 --> 32:53.058
FIND MY MONEY.

32:57.888 --> 32:59.325
ALL RIGHT,
WE CAN DO THIS.

32:59.412 --> 33:01.501
JUST LIKE ONE OF DAD'S
STUPID SCAVENGER HUNTS

33:01.588 --> 33:03.198
WHEN WE WERE 10.

33:03.285 --> 33:04.939
BETWEEN THE SUN AND MOON,
THERE -- THERE'S A BICYCLE,

33:05.026 --> 33:06.854
A TENNIS RACKET,
AND A CAMERA.

33:06.941 --> 33:07.942
DOES THAT MEAN ANYTHING
TO YOU?

33:08.029 --> 33:11.598
CHRISTMAS WHEN I WAS 10.

33:11.685 --> 33:14.035
YEAH. YOU GOT A BIKE.

33:14.122 --> 33:15.863
AND YOU GOT
A TENNIS RACKET.

33:15.950 --> 33:19.519
WHO GOT THE CAMERA?Josh: NOBODY.

33:19.606 --> 33:22.000
NO. DAD DID, AND HE TOOK
A PICTURE OF THE THREE OF US.

33:22.087 --> 33:23.044
WHERE IS IT?

33:23.131 --> 33:24.611
PROBABLY SOMEWHERE
IN THE HOUSE.

33:24.698 --> 33:26.134
FIND IT.

33:35.187 --> 33:36.753
YOU ALL PACKED UP
AND READY TO GO?

33:36.840 --> 33:40.409
I'LL LEAVE WHEN I'M READY.

33:40.496 --> 33:42.237
YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME.

33:42.324 --> 33:45.501
OH, YEAH, I'M SURE YOU'VE GOT IT
ALL UNDER CONTROL.

33:45.588 --> 33:47.634
WHAT COULD POSSIBLY
GO WRONG?

33:47.721 --> 33:49.853
THE OLD MAN
FORGED THE WILLS.

33:49.940 --> 33:51.507
WE HAVE NO IDEA
WHERE THE REAL ONES ARE

33:51.594 --> 33:52.987
OR HOW MUCH
HE EVEN LEFT THESE GUYS.

33:53.074 --> 33:56.121
OH. COME ON.
HE LEFT THEM PLENTY.

33:57.948 --> 34:00.342
I KNEW HIM.

34:00.429 --> 34:02.040
THEN HOW COULD YOU DO THIS
TO HIS FAMILY?

34:04.042 --> 34:08.350
I CAME TO HIM A YEAR AGO.

34:08.437 --> 34:11.223
I TOLD HIM,
"I HAVE MONEY PROBLEMS...

34:11.310 --> 34:12.789
AND I NEED HELP."

34:12.876 --> 34:14.835
AND YOU KNOW
WHAT HE SAID TO ME?

34:14.922 --> 34:16.228
HE SAID...

34:16.315 --> 34:20.058
"MAKE A PLAN.
SEE IT THROUGH."

34:20.145 --> 34:22.582
"MAKE A PLAN.
SEE IT THROUGH."

34:22.669 --> 34:24.671
ADVICE TAKEN.

34:27.848 --> 34:29.893
THE CRIME
ISN'T THE HARD PART.

34:31.286 --> 34:33.027
HARD PART'S
GETTING AWAY WITH IT.

34:35.247 --> 34:37.118
YOU SEE, YOU NEVER KNOW

34:37.205 --> 34:40.643
HOW AN INVESTIGATION
IS GONNA GO...

34:40.730 --> 34:44.778
OR WHAT LITTLE CLUES YOU MIGHT
ACCIDENTALLY LEAVE BEHIND.

34:44.865 --> 34:47.520
I HOPE YOU'VE LEARNED TO SLEEP
WITH ONE EYE OPEN.

34:51.089 --> 34:53.265
Diana: BINGO!

34:53.352 --> 34:55.354
1014 WELLESLEY.

34:55.441 --> 34:57.573
His bank sent us a check he
cashed for an off-the-books job.

34:57.660 --> 34:59.880
WHO LIVES THERE?Nobody.

34:59.967 --> 35:01.403
IT'S BEEN ON THE MARKET
FOR OVER A MONTH.

35:01.490 --> 35:03.623
I'LL BE THERE IN FIVE.
GET ME SOME BACKUP.

35:03.710 --> 35:05.712
You got it.YOU NEED TO HURRY, PETER.

35:05.799 --> 35:07.192
NEAL'S STILL IN THERE
WITH GELLES.

35:13.328 --> 35:14.982
I THOUGHT THE PHOTO
WAS OF THE TWO OF YOU.

35:15.069 --> 35:17.767
IT WAS.
MY FATHER CUT IT IN HALF.

35:17.854 --> 35:19.160
WHERE'S THE PART
WITH YOUR BROTHER?

35:19.247 --> 35:20.944
Josh: HERE.

35:22.511 --> 35:24.948
DO YOU SEE ANYTHING
IN THESE PICTURES?

35:25.035 --> 35:26.428
Josh: NO.
James: NO.

35:26.515 --> 35:28.430
ALL RIGHT. NOTHING BEHIND THEM.
NOTHING ON THE BACK?

35:30.824 --> 35:32.042
Man: MOVE! MOVE!

35:32.130 --> 35:33.914
SAVANNAH,
DO YOU HEAR US?

35:36.134 --> 35:39.093
THEY'RE IN THE SAME PLACE
EXACTLY OPPOSITE EACH OTHER.

35:39.180 --> 35:41.182
WHAT WAS THE LAST LINE OF THE
WILL? IT'S THE SAME IN BOTH.

35:41.269 --> 35:43.184
Josh: SOMETHING LIKE,
"WHEN IT'S ALL SAID AND DONE,

35:43.271 --> 35:44.577
THERE SHOULDN'T BE
ANYTHING BETWEEN YOU."

35:44.664 --> 35:46.144
"IN THE END, THERE SHOULD BE
NOTHING BETWEEN YOU."

35:46.231 --> 35:47.580
"WHICH IS EVERYTHING."

35:47.667 --> 35:49.843
Man: RIGHT HERE.

35:49.930 --> 35:51.323
[ KNOCK ECHOING ]

35:51.410 --> 35:52.628
WE NEED TO SEE
WHAT'S INSIDE HERE.

35:52.715 --> 35:55.501
NO. NOT UNTIL
WE KNOW WHERE SHE IS.

35:55.588 --> 35:57.067
FBI! OPEN UP!

35:58.634 --> 36:00.506
Gelles: BREAK IT!

36:00.593 --> 36:02.986
GET SOMETHING
AND BREAK IT OPEN NOW.JAMES.

36:04.858 --> 36:06.599
GET SOMETHING
AND BREAK IT.

36:06.686 --> 36:07.817
[ GUN COCKS ]

36:11.821 --> 36:13.823
JONES, TAKE HIM DOWN.

36:13.910 --> 36:15.260
[ CELL PHONE VIBRATES ]

36:20.178 --> 36:21.962
Jones: FBI!
Man: DON'T MOVE.

36:22.049 --> 36:24.878
BRETT GELLES,
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

36:24.965 --> 36:27.228
[ CHUCKLES ]
HEY, I TOLD YOU.

36:27.315 --> 36:29.230
YOU CAN TAKE ME
ANYTIME YOU WANT.

36:29.317 --> 36:31.319
YOU WON'T RISK ANYTHING
HAPPENING TO SAVANNAH.

36:31.406 --> 36:32.581
THAT'S RIGHT.

36:32.668 --> 36:33.887
[ BEEPING ]

36:33.974 --> 36:35.932
WE WON'T.

36:36.019 --> 36:37.847
Peter: COME HERE.

36:39.458 --> 36:40.546
[ HANDCUFFS CLICKING ]

36:40.633 --> 36:43.897
SHE'S OKAY.

36:43.984 --> 36:46.204
YOUR DADDY'S WATCHING. YOU WANT TO SAY HI TO HIM?

36:46.291 --> 36:48.380
HI, DADDY!

36:48.467 --> 36:51.774
Peter:
WE'LL SEE YOU IN A BIT.

36:51.861 --> 36:54.212
Man: COME ON. LET'S GO.

36:55.343 --> 36:56.475
COME ON.

37:03.525 --> 37:05.223
DADDY! DADDY!

37:05.310 --> 37:06.485
COME HERE.

37:06.572 --> 37:07.486
COME HERE.

37:13.535 --> 37:15.842
HEY.
HI.

37:15.929 --> 37:17.974
Neal:
YOU FOUND SAVANNAH.

37:18.061 --> 37:19.889
YOU FOUND
THE LAST CLUE.

37:19.976 --> 37:22.109
GUESS WE BOTH
DID OUR PART.
MM.

37:22.196 --> 37:23.937
YOU FIND OUT
WHAT'S INSIDE THE WALL?

37:24.024 --> 37:27.723
NO. JONES BARGED IN
BEFORE WE COULD OPEN IT UP.

37:27.810 --> 37:30.552
AREN'T YOU JUST
A LITTLE CURIOUS?

38:02.497 --> 38:05.500
THE REAL BOOK.

38:05.587 --> 38:08.286
IT'S BRAHE'S ENTIRE COLLECTION
OF MANUSCRIPTS.

38:08.373 --> 38:10.157
AND THE REAL WILL.

38:10.244 --> 38:12.333
OKAY. NOW YOU CAN SAY
YOU TOLD ME SO.

38:12.420 --> 38:14.248
AH, IT'S OKAY, YOU KNOW.

38:14.335 --> 38:18.339
I'LL SAVE IT
FOR ANOTHER TIME.

38:18.426 --> 38:21.995
Neal: THE ROLANDS DONATED
THE ENTIRE BRAHE COLLECTION

38:22.082 --> 38:23.605
TO THE PLANETARIUM.

38:23.692 --> 38:26.216
UNVEILING CEREMONY
THIS SATURDAY --

38:26.304 --> 38:28.131
WE'RE INVITED.
OH HO!

38:28.218 --> 38:30.351
WELL,
I'LL HAVE TO ASK FELIX

38:30.438 --> 38:32.788
IF THEY'VE REMOVED YOU
FROM THEIR NO-FLY LIST.

38:32.875 --> 38:34.442
AFTER THEIR FATHER'S ENDOWMENT
IN THE WILL,

38:34.529 --> 38:35.878
I'LL BET EVEN SATCHMO'S
ALLOWED TO RETURN.

38:35.965 --> 38:38.228
YEAH. HEY.

38:39.578 --> 38:42.972
DOES THIS LOOK LIKE
A COMPASS ROSE?

38:48.195 --> 38:50.197
I THINK IT LOOKS LIKE
REAL-ESTATE FRAUD.

38:50.284 --> 38:51.981
I THINK SO, TOO.
YEAH.

38:52.068 --> 38:53.243
Peter:
SEE YOU TOMORROW, NEAL.YEP.

38:53.331 --> 38:54.419
HEY.

38:56.246 --> 38:57.422
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK
TO NORMAL.

38:57.509 --> 38:58.553
YEAH.

38:59.859 --> 39:02.165
YEAH, IT IS.

39:39.638 --> 39:41.814
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS,
SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYS ]

39:49.125 --> 39:50.518
HOW YOU DOING?

39:50.605 --> 39:52.085
SHE'S ALREADY
TWO MARTINIS IN.

39:52.172 --> 39:53.695
MM. WISH ME LUCK.

39:53.782 --> 39:55.218
YOU DON'T NEED LUCK.

39:55.305 --> 39:56.959
I'M OFF TO SELL OUR DEGAS.

39:57.046 --> 39:59.875
THEN YOUNEED THE LUCK.

40:03.662 --> 40:07.013
VODKA MARTINI, DIRTY, PLEASE.
THANKS.

40:10.016 --> 40:11.060
AGENT MATTHEWS?

40:11.147 --> 40:13.498
HELLO AGAIN.
HELLO.

40:13.585 --> 40:15.674
DID YOU EVER MAKE IT
TO BURKE'S OFFICE?

40:15.761 --> 40:17.763
YES, I DID,
THANKS TO YOU.

40:19.678 --> 40:21.593
I NEVER INTRODUCED MYSELF,
BY THE WAY. I'M SORRY.

40:21.680 --> 40:23.508
CHRIS GATES.
OH.

40:23.595 --> 40:26.380
HELLO, CHRIS.HOW YOU DOING?

40:26.467 --> 40:28.121
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

40:28.208 --> 40:29.992
WELL, YOU'RE NOT THE ONLY ONE
WHO'S A LONG WAY FROM HOME.

40:30.079 --> 40:32.560
I'M ON MY WAY
BACK TO PARIS.

40:34.388 --> 40:36.521
THANKS.
MM.

40:36.608 --> 40:38.044
YOU'RE INTERPOL?

40:38.131 --> 40:40.046
YEAH. YEAH.

40:40.133 --> 40:41.221
WHAT DIVISION?

40:41.308 --> 40:42.788
ART CRIMES.

40:44.398 --> 40:46.356
TO A KINDRED SPIRIT.

40:48.228 --> 40:50.883
YOU HAVE THAT LOOK
ON YOUR FACE.
WHAT LOOK?

40:50.970 --> 40:53.015
I'M SURE YOU'RE IN NEW YORK
FOR THE SAME REASON I AM.

40:53.102 --> 40:54.582
WHICH IS?

40:54.669 --> 40:56.715
CLASSIFIED.

40:56.802 --> 40:58.934
WE'VE SAID TOO MUCH,
OKAY?

40:59.021 --> 41:00.980
I'M SURE AGENT BURKE
SAID THE SAME THING
TO YOU HE SAID TO ME.

41:01.067 --> 41:02.590
SO LET'S JUST --
LET'S TALK ABOUT THE WEATHER.

41:02.677 --> 41:03.939
LET'S TALK ABOUT
SOMETHING INNOCUOUS.

41:04.026 --> 41:06.507
HOW ABOUT WE BOTH SAY,
ON THREE?

41:06.594 --> 41:08.074
WHAT?

41:08.161 --> 41:09.554
NO. NO.

41:09.641 --> 41:11.077
AT THE SAME TIME?

41:11.164 --> 41:12.295
MM-HMM.

41:13.732 --> 41:15.429
ALL RIGHT.

41:15.516 --> 41:16.822
OKAY.

41:16.909 --> 41:19.085
1, 2, 3...1, 2, 3...

41:19.172 --> 41:20.042
NAZI S...

41:20.129 --> 41:22.088
OH. NOT COOL.

41:22.175 --> 41:23.872
YOU'RE TRICKY.

41:23.959 --> 41:25.352
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT?

41:25.439 --> 41:26.788
IT'S INCREDIBLE, THOUGH,
ISN'T IT?

41:26.875 --> 41:29.312
WHAT, THAT AGENT BURKE
THINKS ALL THIS ART

41:29.399 --> 41:31.576
IS JUST FLOATING AROUND
OUT THERE OR...

41:31.663 --> 41:35.449
CAN YOU IMAGINE
IF IT IS?

41:35.536 --> 41:38.887
OH, GOD, I WISH THAT I HAD
CLEARANCE TO SEE THAT MANIFEST.

41:38.974 --> 41:40.933
[ SIGHS ]

41:41.020 --> 41:43.457
YEAH, WELL, YOU CAN STOP
FISHING HERE.

41:43.544 --> 41:45.981
I MEAN, HE DIDN'T -- HE DIDN'T
SHOW IT TO ME, EITHER, SO...

41:48.723 --> 41:50.159
ANY THEORIES?

41:50.246 --> 41:53.249
UM, APPARENTLY...

41:53.336 --> 41:55.948
THEY ONLY FOUND
ONE PAGE, SO...

41:56.035 --> 41:57.471
SO IT'S A PARTIAL LIST.

41:57.558 --> 41:59.604
MOST OF WHAT WAS ON THE SUB
IS STILL UNACCOUNTED FOR.

41:59.691 --> 42:01.301
RIGHT.

42:01.388 --> 42:04.870
BUT IF ANYONE TRIES TO SELL
ANYTHING THAT'S ON THAT LIST...

42:04.957 --> 42:06.872
WE'RE GONNA HEAR ABOUT IT.

42:06.959 --> 42:08.003
AND WE'RE GONNA NAIL 'EM.

42:08.090 --> 42:09.222
YES!

42:09.309 --> 42:11.441
YES, WE ARE.

42:11.529 --> 42:12.704
BAM.

42:12.791 --> 42:14.314
[ CHUCKLES ]

42:15.968 --> 42:19.101
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME FOR A MINUTE?
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

42:19.188 --> 42:21.364
[ Dialing ]

42:21.451 --> 42:24.280
[ Ringing ]

42:24.367 --> 42:25.847
MOZZIE. WHERE ARE YOU?

42:25.934 --> 42:29.329
YOU CANNOT -- I REPEAT --
YOU CANNOT SELL THE PIECE.

42:30.722 --> 42:32.637
WE GOT A BIG PROBLEM.
